name: Google Threat Intelligence
description: Supercharge your Splunk SOAR with Google Threat Intelligence, unifying unparalleled threat analysis directly within your security operations. This app provides context-rich reputation and deep analysis for indicators by fusing three powerful sources: the vast, real-time crowdsourced intelligence of VirusTotal, the frontline breach expertise and actor tracking of Mandiant, and the global threat visibility from Google's own network. Go beyond simple lookups by ingesting curated threat signals from Mandiant-driven Attack Surface Management and Digital Threat Monitoring, along with Google's real-time IOC streams, to automate response with unmatched context and confidence

ingestion_type.description: Type of data to retrieve and ingest

days.description: Lookback Days: Number of days of historical data to retrieve (max: 5) (Applicable for all three ingestion types)

limit.description: Limit: Maximum number of objects to fetch per poll (max: 1000) (Applicable for all three ingestion types)

descriptors_only.description: Descriptors Only: Includes only object descriptors, not full VT objects (IOC Stream)

monitor_id.description: Monitor ID: Filter alerts by the specified monitor ID(s). Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

status.description: Status: Filter alerts by status. Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

alert_type.description: Alert Type: Filter alerts by alert type. Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

search.description: Search String: Search alerts and triggering documents using a Lucene query with text values joined by AND/OR (DTM Alerts)

match_value.description: Match Value: Filter alerts by specified match value. Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

tags.description: Tags: Filter alerts by tags. Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

severity.description: Severity: Filter alerts by specified severity. Supports multiple comma-separated values (DTM Alerts)

mscore_gte.description: MScore GTE: Filter alerts with mscores greater than or equal to the given value (DTM Alerts)

search_string.description: Search String (ASM Issues) (Fields last_seen_after, last_seen_before, and first_seen_after will be ignored)
